race.comment: STRATO KEN (3) surprised third-up, beaten a nose over 1200m at Hobart. John Allen is engaged and he won't have to improve much to take this out. RUSHONOVA (10) has found a place in both starts racing forward and will be fitter again. Has a wide gate to manage this evening but has Luke Currie engaged replacing the 3kg apprentice. She can feature with average luck. TEAM HEIST (6) has switched from a Victorian yard and will come into her own over longer journeys. Has good ability and if she's wound up is likely to be running into it. The betting should provide a clue to that. DIZZ BOOGIE TIME (8) debuts and owns a Longford trial win. Has a 2kg claim and looks set to race well.
